{
  "texts": [
    "Though the feature distributions for the AI-generated essays were indeed closer to one sociodemographic group than another, as seen in Figure 3 and Table 3 for example, they were also quite distinct from those human groups.",
    "This points to two reasonable interpretations of the similarity between human and AI-generated text: a distributional perspective and a sampling perspective (see Figure 7 for a conceptual diagram).",
    "First, we might consider a distributional perspective (not to be confused with (Bellemare et al, 2017)).",
    "If the distribution of the writing style features is so distinctive and unaligned with any human style of writing, future studies might examine the extent to which people consider LLM-generated text unhuman and artificial.",
    "Second, we might consider a sampling perspective where we might focus less on the curves of the distributions of writing features and more on the peaks and expected characteristics."
  ]
}